-- Entergy to shut Waterford reactor ahead of Gustav
-- 
-- Sun Aug 31, 2008 4:15pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/08/31/us-storm-gustav-utilities-waterford-idUSN3137762820080831

 

 HOUSTON  (Reuters) - Entergy Corp's 1,152-megawatt Waterford nuclear plant in Louisiana was preparing to shut the reactor late Sunday as Hurricane Gustav barreled toward the U.S. Gulf coast, said the company and the U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission. 

 (Reporting by  Erwin Seba )